==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Entity
<hw>En"ti*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Entities</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[LL. <ets>entitas</ets>,
fr. L. <ets>ens</ets>, <ets>entis</ets>, thing, prop. p. pr. of
<ets>esse</ets> to be: cf. F. <ets>entit⟦eacute⟧</ets>. See
<er>Essence</er>, <er>Is</er>.]</ety> <def>A real being, whether in
thought (as an ideal conception) or in fact; being; essence;
existence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Self-subsisting <qex>entities</qex>, such as our own
personality.</q> <rj><qau>Shairp.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Fortune is no real <qex>entity</qex>, . . . but a mere relative
signification.</q> <rj><qau>Bentley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ento-</ent>⟦br⟧
